      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_ExecReorgRebuildIndex",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to manage index fragmentation in a specified SQL Server database. It evaluates the fragmentation level of indexes and decides whether to reorganize or rebuild them based on a specified threshold. Additionally, it can execute or print the SQL commands for these operations and update the statistics for the affected indexes."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves dynamic SQL execution, cursor usage, and conditional logic, which adds to its complexity. It requires a good understanding of SQL Server indexing, fragmentation, and performance tuning."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
